H0.text: Who is the last English-born player to win the men's singles title at Wimbledon. Andy Murray

H1.text: Who is the last English-born player to win the men's singles title at Wimbledon. Tim Henman

H2.text: Who is the last English-born player to win the men's singles title at Wimbledon. Greg Rusedski

H3.text: Who is the last English-born player to win the men's singles title at Wimbledon. Fred Perry

A4.text: Fred Perry was born in Stockport, England in 1909.

A5.text: Prior to Andy Murray in 2013, Perry was the last British player to win the men's Wimbledon championship.
